{{Infobox government agency | agency_name = National Electoral Commission | type = Commission | nativename = {{native phrase|sw|Tume ya Taifa ya Uchaguzi}} | logo = National Electoral Commission (Tanzania) Logo.png | picture = | picture_width = | picture_caption = | formed = {{Start date|1993|01|14|df=yes}} | preceding1 = | preceding2 = <!-- up to |preceding6= --> | dissolved = | superseding = | agency_type = Autonomous government institution | jurisdiction = | headquarters = [[Dar es Salaam]], [[Tanzania]] | motto = | employees = | budget = | chief1_name = [[Damian Lubuva]] | chief1_position = Chairman | chief2_name = | chief2_position = <!-- up to |chief9_name= --> | keydocument1 = [https://web.archive.org/web/20150421001106/http://www.judiciary.go.tz/downloads/constitution.pdf Constitution of Tanzania, Article 74(1)] | website = {{URL|www.nec.go.tz}} | footnotes = | embed = }}
The '''National Electoral Commission''' ('''NEC''') is the national [[election commission]] of [[Tanzania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.judiciary.go.tz/downloads/constitution.pdf|title=Constitution of Tanzania|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=2 May 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421001106/http://www.judiciary.go.tz/downloads/constitution.pdf|archivedate=21 April 2015|df=}}</ref>
==Responsibilities== Article 74(6) of the constitution states its responsibilities: *Register voters for the union presidential and parliamentary elections. *Supervise the conduct of the presidential and parliamentary elections *Review and demarcate the electoral boundaries *Perform any other function as per the law such as organize referendums.
